like a bird in a cage.

269
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:59,160
That's probably why some people
get on the roaming buses that

270
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:00,320
travel to the other cities.

271
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:06,720
They get to experience things
that the rest of us don't.

272
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,440
I was jealous.

273
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:11,080
I wanted to be one
of those people,

274
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:14,480
so I decided to come here.

275
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:19,080
But my parents didn't share
my enthusiasm and told me no.

276
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,560
So you ran away, huh?

277
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:24,200
And that's the reason why
I have this glamorous job.

278
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:26,000
It's hard work, but
it does pay well,

279
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,480
and a Military Arts
education isn't cheap.

280
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:30,200
But that's where my
true passion lies.

281
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,160
Not that I'd expect
you to understand that.

282
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,640
Well, back to work.

283
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:41,440
Hm?

284
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:43,920
We need to finish up since
the competition's tomorrow.

285
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:44,720
Wait.

286
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:45,600
It's tomorrow?

287
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,400
Oh yeah.

288
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,640
Did I not mention that before?

289
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:52,640
If you knew we had to
clean all this tonight,

290
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:54,640
then why did to let us
spend so much time talking?

291
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:57,640
I told you it was gonna be
a long story, so quit griping.

292
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:59,160
LAYFON: But I've
gotta get some sleep.

293
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,400
If I don't, I'll be
no good tomorrow.

294
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,200
NINA: Hey.

295
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,160
You had the time to talk,
so you got the time to work.

296
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,000
Move it!

297
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:04,880
LAYFON: It's getting late.

298
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:05,720
NINA: Who care?

299
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:06,520
Work!

300
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,440
LAYFON: I am!

301
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,280
NINA: Go faster!

302
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:14,360
So sleepy.

303
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,320
So sleepy.

304
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,400
It's good that you're
made of such strong stuff,

305
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,280
because if you weren't, we
would have had to withdraw,

306
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:20,760
so thanks for making it.

307
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:27,680
Let me wish you all good luck.

308
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:29,160
If anyone needs
luck today, it's

309
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:32,360
you and your platoon, maggot.

310
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,840
With you in command,
I'll be surprised

311
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:36,400
if your unit lasts more
than five minutes out there.

312
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:45,720
This match will
determine our standing

313
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:48,600
in the next municipal
challenge, so stay sharp.

314
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:55,520
I sure hope Layfie does well.

315
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:57,360
Of course he
will, especially now

316
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:59,560
that he's got one of Mayshen's
delicious homemade meals

317
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:00,720
in his belly.

318
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:03,360
Oh my.

319
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:05,120
Why did I get
a chill just now?

320
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,000
The rules are simple.

321
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:14,360
The 17th platoon will attack and
the 16th platoon will defend.

322
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,440
He's the head
of Military Arts.

323
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:18,880
Treat this like a real
municipal challenge.

324
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:19,720
Yes, sir.

325
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,800
Now take your positions.

326
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:23,080
WOMAN (OVER SPEAKER):
The competition

327
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:25,640
between the 16th and 17th
platoons will now commence.

328
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:28,440
As a safety precaution,
we must request

329
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,520
that all spectators
remain seated

330
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,920
behind the protective
barriers at all times.

331
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:39,440
NINA: Since we're attacking,
there are only two ways to win.

332
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:41,280
Wipe out the enemy
platoon or take down

333
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,680
the flag behind their lines.

334
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,640
LAYFON: And how can the
defending team win this?

335
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:47,120
NINA: They can either protect
the flag until time runs out,

336
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:49,680
or they can take down the
opposing force's leader.

337
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:53,120
In this match,
that leader is me.

338
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,800
Since I'm their primary target,
I'm gonna act as a decoy

339
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,080
and lure them away.

340
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:58,360
They'll be one fearless move.

341
00:16:58,360 --> 00:16:59,840
NINA: ‐ Layfon,
get to that flag.

342
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,400
Sharnid, you cover him.

343
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:03,160
Roger that, boss.

344
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:06,040
Enemies are approaching.

345
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,000
NINA: Restoration.

346
00:17:13,120 --> 00:17:13,880
Gotcha.

347
00:17:21,320 --> 00:17:23,400
Watch out.

348
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,480
Get out of here!

349
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,920
Restoration.

350
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:26,720
Sharnid.

351
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:29,480
Layfon could use
a little backup.

352
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:33,880
That's easier said than done.

353
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:36,560
That new student's
responses are pretty pathetic.

354
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:38,400
And his Kei channeling
is rather poor too.

355
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,320
KARIAN (ON PHONE): Trust me.

356
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:41,520
Don't write him off yet.

357
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:43,360
What exactly are you hiding?

358
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,920
KARIAN (ON PHONE): Zuellni
always gets students

359
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,200
who are young and immature.

360
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,240
Perhaps the importance of
this match hasn't sunk in

361
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:49,560
and he thinks it's
just child's play.

362
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:51,400
MAN (ON SPEAKER): He needs
to look at it more like it's

363
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,560
a matter of life and death.

364
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:56,040
I tried to impart how
important his skills were

365
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:58,760
for this city's survival,
but for some reason,

366
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:01,840
our new student is still
lacking in motivation.

367
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:03,880
Seems he's not the only one.

368
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:07,240
Your sister is as well.

369
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,680
Those two are uninspired.

370
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,280
And Sharnid's undisciplined.

371
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:14,240
The whole platoon's a mess.

372
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:16,760
You should reassign Nina
Antalk to another platoon

373
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:18,520
so she has a chance to succeed.

374
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:19,720
KARIAN (ON PHONE):
offered, but she

375
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,480
refused, so let's see
how she and her platoon

376
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:22,520
do in this match.

377
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:23,440
Who knows?

378
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,400
They might surprise you.

379
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,240
I doubt it.

380
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:27,080
Knowing this bunch, I think
the only thing they're

381
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,560
gonna achieve is failure.

382
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:30,400
Sometimes the fear
of failure is all

383
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:33,800
the motivation that one needs.

384
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,040
Restoration.

385
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:39,040
NINA: Sharnid, what gives?

386
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,560
Why aren't you helping Layfon?

387
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:42,360
He's too close to
his sparring partner,

388
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:44,160
so I can't get a clear shot.

389
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:46,280
NINA (VOICEOVER): Felli,
what's taking so long?

390
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:47,640
Why haven't you found
the enemy's base?

391
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:49,800
'Cause I'm
currently at my limit.

392
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:17,800
LAYFON (VOICEOVER): Keep
my strength a secret.

393
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:20,800
[SCREAMING]

394
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,280
Layfon!

395
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:34,720
FELLI (VOICEOVER):
Layfon's vanished.

396
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:36,720
Damage unknown.

397
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:37,720
Oh no.

398
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,400
[SHOUTING]

399
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,200
SHARNID: Dammit.

400
00:19:52,200 --> 00:19:53,440
Finally, a clear shot.

401
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,400
Thanks a lot, tubby.

402
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:04,000
LAYFON (VOICEOVER): Are you sure
it's OK if we lose this thing?

403
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,160
Nina.

404
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:26,600
You haven't improved
over the last two years

405
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,400
at all, have you?

406
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,760
I'm not surprised.

407
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:31,640
Argh!

408
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,280
It's impossible.

409
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:35,520
You still had that
much strength left?

410
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:36,920
I sure did.

411
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:39,920
Now I'm gonna use the rest
of it and take you down!

412
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:47,160
Just like last
time, you came close,

413
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:49,560
but ultimately you failed.

414
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:52,080
[SHOUTING]

415
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,080
Get out of there.

416
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,080
Run.

417
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,520
[SHOUTING]

418
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:01,640
Start the countdown.

419
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:03,520
This match is almost over.

420
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:05,520
KARIAN (ON PHONE): I wouldn't
be so sure about that.

421
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:06,320
Come on.

422
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:07,720
At this point, the
17th platoon would

423
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,720
need a real miracle to win.

424
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:11,360
If you want to fight alone,
then you're gonna lose alone.

425
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:14,280
How does it feel to know
you failed once again?

426
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:15,080
NINA (VOICEOVER): No.

427
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,520
I can't lose again.

428
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:20,880
But I can't hold on much longer.

429
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,720
I can't lose again.

430
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,480
But I can't hold on much longer.

